Windows Functions :- Performs calculations on subset of data without losing details.

1. What is data aggregation?  
SELECT  
COUNT(*) count,
AVG(sales) avg,
SUM(sales) sum,
MAX(sales) MAX,
MIN(sales) MIN
FROM
Sales.Orders

SELECT  
CustomerID,
COUNT(*) count,
AVG(sales) avg,
SUM(sales) sum,
MAX(sales) MAX,
MIN(sales) MIN
FROM
Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID

Window Functions Vs Aggregation functions

When using Aggregation function, will lose level of information where as using windows functions won't lose level of informaiton 
with aggregated values.

Group Aggregation :- Simple Aggregations       Window:- Aggregations + Keep Details
                   Simple Data Analysis                  Advanced Data Analysis.

--Find total sales across all orders
SELECT 
SUM(sales)
FROM
Sales.Orders

--Find total sales for each product
SELECT 
productid,
SUM(sales)
FROM
Sales.Orders
GROUP BY ProductID


--Find total sales for each product
--Additionally provide details such order id,order date
SELECT 
OrderID,
OrderDate,
productid,
SUM(sales) over(PARTITION BY productid) sum_of
FROM
Sales.Orders

PARTITION BY ==>   syntax:-fun() over (PARTITION BY <column1,column2... columnn> ORDER BY <column1,column2...column-n> FRAME CLAUSE)

EXAMPLE:- AVG(sales) OVER (PARTITION BY Category ORDER BY orderdate)

--Find total sales for each product,product-status
--Additionally provide details such order id,order date
SELECT 
OrderID,
OrderDate,
productid,
OrderStatus,
sales,
SUM(sales) over() total_sales,
SUM(sales) over(PARTITION BY productid) sum_productid,
SUM(sales) over(PARTITION BY productid,orderstatus) sum_productid_orderstatus
FROM
Sales.Orders

ORDER BY CLAUSE   ===>         For Aggregate functions ORDER BY is optional.

SELECT
OrderID,
OrderDate,
Sales,
RANK() OVER (ORDER BY sales desc) RANK
FROM
Sales.Orders


FRAME CLAUSE :-  ROWS UNBOUNDING PRECEDING

ROWS BETWEEN CURRENT ROW AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING

ROWS ==> ROWS,RANGE
CURRENT ROW ===> CURRENT ROW,N PRECEDING,UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING ===> CURRENT ROW,N FOLLOWING, UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING

SHORT CUT :- ROWS 2 PRECEDING,ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING (Always short cut is applicable for PRECEDING ONLY) 

DEFAULT FUNCTIONALITY is ==> ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW)




Rules for Windows function
1. We can use window function only in select and order by calsuse
2. we can't use nesting windows functions.
3. first WHERE CLause executes then windows function executes.
4. Always use group by column used in windows function as well.

SELECT
CustomerID,
SUM(sales) sum,
RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(sales) DESC) RANK
FROM
Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID






